                <note rend="inline" type="source">365D.1163/141: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 12, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>127. Department’s instruction no. 513, July 19.<note n="11" xml:id="d582fn11">Not
                        printed.</note> Department is informed by Presbyterian Board of Foreign
                    Missions that its representatives in Ethiopia, Dr. John A. Cremer and the
                    Reverend Duncan C. Henry, have been expelled by the Italian authorities
                    following expropriation of mission property at Addis Ababa.</p>
                <p>Please investigate and report by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
